'''''Movie''''' is a [[video game]] written by Duško Dimitrijević for the [[ZX Spectrum]] and [[Amstrad CPC]] and was published by [[Imagine Software]] in [[1986 in video gaming|1986]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite book |url=http://archive.org/details/crash-magazine-26 |title=Crash Magazine Issue 26 |date=March 1986 |publisher=Newsfield Publications Ltd |year=1986 |location=UK |pages=20–22 |language=en}}</ref>

==Plot==

'''''Movie''''' is set in [[New York City]] in the 1930s. The player takes the role of Jack Marlow, a [[private investigator]] who must enter the headquarters of mob boss Bugs Malloy in order to retrieve an audiotape.<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://archive.org/details/ace-magazine-12 |title=ACE Magazine Issue 12 |date=September 1988 |year=1988 |location=UK |pages=78}}</ref> In order to help him complete this task, Marlow needs the help of a girl called Tanya. Unfortunately, she has an identical twin called Vanya who is allied to Malloy and who will deliberately lead him into trouble.

==Gameplay==
The game is an [[arcade adventure]] which uses an [[isometric projection|isometric]] display to portray the action, described by several publications as similar to that of ''[[Knightlore]].''<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://archive.org/details/zxcomputing-magazine-1986-04 |title=ZX Computing Magazine (April 1986) |date=April 1986 |publisher=Argus Specialist Publications |year=1986 |location=UK |pages=53 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |url=http://archive.org/details/sinclair-user-magazine-048 |title=Sinclair User Magazine Issue 048 |date=March 1986}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |url=http://archive.org/details/Computer_Gamer_Issue_12_1986-03_Argus_Press_GB |title=Computer Gamer - Issue 12 |date=March 1986 |publisher=Argus Press |year=1986 |location=UK |pages=63–64}}</ref> Movement is achieved by rotating the main character and moving him forward. The player can also access a panel of [[Computer icon|icons]] which allow Marlow to carry out certain actions such as dropping and taking items, shooting his firearm, punching, throwing an item or talking.<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://archive.org/details/sinclair-user-magazine-048 |title=Sinclair User Magazine Issue 048 |date=March 1986 |year=1986 |location=UK |pages=58 |language=en}}</ref> The latter is performed using speech bubbles in which the player can type out words and phrases using the keyboard.

==Reception==
